msgid "Flinkform — Form Submissions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Privacy.php:59
msgid "When a visitor submits a form built with Flinkform, the plugin stores the submitted field values (name, email, message, etc.) in a dedicated database table on this website. No IP addresses or browser user-agent strings are collected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Privacy.php:61
msgid "Submissions are retained until a site administrator deletes them (individually or in bulk), until the plugin is uninstalled, or — when a per-form retention period is configured — until they are older than that period, after which a daily routine deletes them automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Privacy.php:63
msgid "Flinkform does not send any submission data to external services. (Add-ons such as Flinkform Pro may add integrations — e.g. webhooks or SMTP delivery — that transmit data to third parties; those add their own privacy disclosures when active.)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Privacy.php:65
msgid "The built-in spam protection (proof-of-work challenge) runs entirely in the visitor's browser and on this server — no data is sent to any external anti-spam service."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Privacy.php:67
msgid "Flinkform sets one short-lived, strictly necessary cookie (\"flinkform_flash\", lifetime ~60 seconds, httpOnly) — and only when a submission fails validation, to carry the error message across the page reload. No tracking, analytics or marketing cookies are ever set."
msgstr ""

